text: Hey arya-ers. I printed up some blank floorplans in case you'd be willing to sketch in some of your ideas of how the office layout could be. Don't worry, it is not some kind of "we'll pick one  of those" sorts of things, but more a way to start creating ideas about layout/flow. The printouts are by the foamcore "Project Arya" sign in the middle wall bay in 390 area. The scale is off (I inflated them to use more of the paper) but lengthwise the distance between columns is 26'. and there's a weird stair spur at the top left which is because they accidentally used floor 2 to give us a blank floor. We don't have that spur! Oh and bathroom layouts are supposed to flipped to keep the doors further away from the elevator.

text: I've forwarded an invite for Thursday 10 am to the Arya Committee people, which is when the architect and Beam will be stopping by to chat with us, and hear at least our design principle thoughts. This is a session to get them aligning with us, but it isn't the final guidance we're giving them yet. Others are welcome to join, just add the meeting to your calendar and maybe slack me so I know you're comin. :simple_smile:
